    <h1>Groups &amp; Clubs</h1>
    <p class="lead">The Lenches punch well above their weight for community life. Below are our local groups — some have their own websites (we link to those), and for others we host their information here.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Groups we host</h2>

    <div class="card" id="glads">
      <h3 class="mt0">GLADS — Great Lenches Amateur Dramatic Society</h3>
      <p>The Lenches' very own amateur dramatic society: a fun, sociable group of all ages who perform around the villages to raise money for the local community — over £12,600 donated to date. Established in 2010, they've staged pantomimes, comedy dramas and murder mysteries.</p>
      <p>Everyone is welcome, whether you fancy treading the boards or helping backstage with scenery, costumes or make-up. Email <a href="mailto:John@tookney.swiftserve.net">John@tookney.swiftserve.net</a> or find them on <a href="https://www.facebook.com/gladslenches" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Facebook</a>.</p>
      <div class="gallery">
        <img src="https://storage.mlcdn.com/account_image/2093769/obU8XTjN8a7rHOUu_Glads2.jpeg" alt="GLADS production" loading="lazy">
        <img src="https://storage.mlcdn.com/account_image/2093769/11wlFpp2NFjftLnT_Glads3.jpeg" alt="GLADS production" loading="lazy">
        <img src="https://storage.mlcdn.com/account_image/2093769/cno0lPyMr365W765_Glads1.jpeg" alt="GLADS production" loading="lazy">
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card" id="walking">
      <h3 class="mt0">The Lenches Walking Group</h3>
      <p>The group meets one morning each week in the Lenches Club car park, then drives together to the start of a circular walk, finishing with a pub lunch before heading home. The meeting day rotates each week — a Monday one week, a Tuesday the next — so most people can join in at some point.</p>
      <p>No joining or membership fees, and new members are always warmly welcomed. For more information, contact Pete Marston on <a href="mailto:petemarston@msn.com">petemarston@msn.com</a> or 01386 872717.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card" id="orchard">
      <h3 class="mt0">Yates Community Orchard</h3>
      <p>Donated to the community by David and Carol Yates and opened in 2008 by HRH the Duke of Kent, the orchard now has a gazebo for shade and shelter. It's used in term time by the local first school for Forest School, and kept in good order by volunteers — more always welcome.</p>
      <p>You're welcome to picnic in the orchard and to pick any fruit that's ready. Please note there are active beehives in a segregated section, so take appropriate care. Contact: Jonathan Hazlewood, <a href="mailto:jbpmh1013@gmail.com">jbpmh1013@gmail.com</a>.</p>
      <div class="gallery">
        <img src="https://storage.mlcdn.com/account_image/2093769/LqJwPULmC76psJjY_blossom.jpeg" alt="Orchard blossom" loading="lazy">
        <img src="https://storage.mlcdn.com/account_image/2093769/jxgDg8W0nM7bBpEy_gazebo1.jpeg" alt="Orchard gazebo" loading="lazy">
        <img src="https://storage.mlcdn.com/account_image/2093769/6nLHqFgu9knYbGHY_gazebo2.jpeg" alt="Orchard gazebo" loading="lazy">
      </div>
